description:
IN THIS EPISODE, we dive deeper into publishing with our returning guest, Stephen Apola. We move beyond the mechanics of who sells and distributes books to explore the real impact of literature on individuals and society. From the historical roots of Seventh-day Adventist publishing to the modern-day challenges and opportunities, this episode offers a comprehensive look at the transformative power of the written word.

🎙️ Highlights:
The history and mission of Adventist publishing
The role of Ellen White in shaping the Adventist approach to publishing
The correlation between literature work and church growth
The importance of physical books in an increasingly digital world
The upcoming largest book distribution in human history: The Great Controversy Project.
Follow for more about publishing next week with guest Almir Marroni, director of Publishing Ministries.

The Seventh-day Adventist Church has been an established denomination since 1863. It is a global Christian family with over 21 million members who hold the Bible as the ultimate authority. We are believers who promise to help people understand the Bible to find freedom, healing, and hope in Jesus.
Want to learn more about the Seventh-day Adventist Church?
